<!-- BEGIN app snippet: productFAQ --><script type="application/ld+json" class="ws_schema">{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How to build a gaming setup?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Gaming room setups can be as small as a chair and a pc or as elaborate as the royal family's Christmas traditions. The sky is the limit when it comes to choosing accessories and their features for your gaming setup. In general, the gaming room setup consists of additions like a monitor, keyboard, mouse and headphones with a mic to communicate while gaming. A dedicated chair and desk can be bought to make the setup more comfortable. In case you are on a budget, you can go for our economical gaming chairs \u0026 desks that deliver comfort without breaking the bank. "}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How to decorate a gaming room?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The gaming room should be decorated in a way that reflects your personality. You can go for different themes, based on a game you like or a character you relate to. Solid colours can also be mixed and matched to turn your gaming room into a style statement. You can also showcase your accessories on shelves with different posters or paintings on the wall. When it comes to decorating any space, nothing is off-limits as long as you don’t start feeling overwhelmed with it. Focus on fixed things like lighting or wall colour more than the variables like shelves or cabinets, as you can’t change the fixed things easily. "}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How to soundproof a gaming room on a budget with a gaming chair in the UK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Generally, people think that soundproofing is always an expensive thing to do. It is quite right because if you get professional help, it can cost you from £300 to £2,000 or more, depending on your room size. But, focusing on small things like setup placement or furniture choices can make a lot of difference. Decorate your room with thick rugs and curtains along with fabric upholstered furniture that minimises the eco and absorbs a lot of sound. These are not the perfect solution, but can help you focus on the games. "}}]}</script><!-- END app snippet -->





  


