        </div>
      </div><p class="text-theme-light reading-width mx-auto text-center">Gaurav Singh | 
<time datetime="2025-05-12T11:10:27Z">May 12, 2025</time>
</p><div class="article__content reading-width rte article-content mt-12 mx-auto">
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
            
                
                
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
              
        
          

        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
            
                
                
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
        
            
            
        
            
              
            
            
            
                      
        
        <p dir="ltr"><span>Gaming has become a part of our lifestyle. The increasing popularity of Esports and a lot of people becoming full-time gamers has grown the need for a dedicated room to play games. It becomes a must for people who stream their game-play as it increases the overall aesthetics &amp; affects the viewership. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>From choosing the right chair to selecting the correct wall colours, there is a lot when it comes to creating your perfect gamer’s den. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>In this article, we will talk about </span><span>gaming room ideas</span><span> that you should focus on while building your gaming room because it's all about levelling up, one game at a time.  </span></p>
<h2><strong>Technology &amp; Gaming Accessories</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><span>Many people argue that skills are more important for becoming a great gamer. But we believe the accessories and technology used by a gamer also play a major role in it. Technology is the key to improving your gameplay. From wide or curved displays to internet connection or VR technology, there are a lot of different things that can help you become a better gamer. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Dual/Triple Monitor Setup</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Modern gaming setup with multiple monitors, a sleek PC, and professional studio lights." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/gaming-room.webp?v=1747037025" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span></span><span>From immersive gameplay to in-game communications, a display is one of the most used accessories in a gaming room setup. Gaming is more fun when you play it on a monitor with good resolution. We know that one is never enough when it comes to monitors. So, you can even combine 2 or 3 displays to get the most out of your gaming setup. Compact spaces can go for wall-mounted options. Some things to focus on:</span><b></b></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Refresh Rate:</strong> </span><span>Important for smooth gameplay, go for a display with a 144Hz or higher refresh rate.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Size &amp; Resolution:</strong> </span><span>Go for a display with thin bezels, 1440p for affordability or 4K for great visuals. <br></span><span></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>GPU Compatibility:</strong><span> Check if your GPU can handle multiple displays, and choose accordingly. </span>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Headphones &amp; Sound Systems</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Young man wearing black gaming headphones around his neck, sitting on a chair in a gaming room." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/man-with-headphones.webp?v=1747037066" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span></span><span>Sounds make all the difference. From hearing the footsteps of your enemy to the sound of your gun blazing at them, a great accessory to hear the in-game sounds is extremely necessary. Some people like headphones with noise-cancelling features, so they love the sound bars. The choice is yours to make. Things to consider: </span><b></b></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Headphones</strong>: </span><span>Go for noise-cancelling, they minimise distractions &amp; increase focus on the game.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Sound Bars: </strong><span>Used to get a surround sound in the whole room, making the game more immersive.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Other Accessories &amp; Tech</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="close up of a mechanical gaming keyboard and mouse placed on a large brown leather desk mat." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/gaming-room-items.webp?v=1747037399" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span></span><span>Displays are important. But, they can’t help you improve your gameplay without the proper support of other accessories &amp; tech. From the right keyboard to a stable internet connection, a lot of small but significant things make or break the whole gaming experience. </span><b></b></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Keyboard</strong>: </span><span>Mechanical to lightweight, you can even go for an RGB-lighted one.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Mouse</strong>: </span><span>Go for a mouse with a higher DPI, as it helps you navigate in the game.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Internet</strong>: </span><span>High-speed internet helps you get a lag-free gaming experience.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="ltr"><strong>Never Compromise On Comfort</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><span>Comfort should be the priority while building your gaming setup. With hours &amp; hours of gaming sessions, a setup that can ease the stress on your body can really help you focus more on your gaming. From comfortable chairs to desks with different features, you have a lot of options from which you can choose the best gaming furniture that helps you improve your game-playing experience. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Ergonomic Gaming Chair</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Professional gaming chair and desk setup with multiple screens and vibrant blue lighting." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/gaming-chair.webp?v=1747037962" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span>Choosing the right gaming chair is very crucial for creating an ultimate gaming setup. There has been a lot of research on the effects of a dedicated gaming chair on a player's gameplay and the results are quite positive. </span><span>As the gaming sessions usually last for a long time, prioritise comfort over looks while picking your </span><a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/products/best-gaming-chair" title="Best Gaming Chair"><span>best gaming chair</span></a><span>.</span><span> Some of the features that you can look for are…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Ergonomic Design</strong><span><strong>:</strong> High backrest or better lumbar support to keep you comfortable.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Adjustable Armrests</strong><span><strong>: </strong>At least 3d or 4d, to prevent strain on arms while playing games.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Seat Cushioning</strong><span><strong>: </strong>Makes your sitting easy and reduces pressure on your legs. <br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<meta charset="utf-8"> <b id="docs-internal-guid-14c13d0f-7fff-31ad-9b92-837790fdd024"><span>Reclining Mechanism: </span></b>It helps you adjust the <a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/collections/office-chairs" title="desk chairs">desk chairs</a>’ posture to your liking.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Wide Desk For Extra Space</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="modern gaming setup with a curved monitor, keyboard and CPU placed on a white desk, two controllers hanging on a pegboard." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/wide-desk.webp?v=1747038104" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span>A gaming desk is usually the last thing people think about when building a gaming setup. But, choosing the right desk for your setup can elevate your gaming experience. </span><span>If you are going to spend a lot of time gaming in the setup, the </span><a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/collections/desks" title="computer desk"><span>computer desk</span></a><span> is just as important as the chair.</span><span> Some of the features to look out for are…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Surface Area:</strong> </span><span>It should have enough space to place your PCs and other essentials.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Build Quality:</strong> </span><span>Sturdiness depends on the build quality. So don’t compromise on that.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Height Adjustability:</strong> </span><span>Some of them come with it, for better ergonomic support.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Storage:</strong> </span><span>Dedicated space for your CPU or cables can help you focus on your gameplay.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Lighting For The Vibe</strong></h2>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/lighting-in-gaming-room.webp?v=1747047738" alt="Cool gaming room decor featuring a world map, neon lights, and a computer setup with RGB CPU." style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span><meta charset="utf-8">Lighting plays a vital role in making a room suitable for gaming. With options like RGB or customizable lights in the market, you have a lot of variants to choose from. Go for the lights that can reduce the strain on your eyes, to help you play for a longer period and win a lot of battles. You can also style your gaming room with glow-in-the-dark paint or articles matching with your <a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/blogs/inspiration/finding-best-office-chair-uk-made-easy" title="best office chair uk">best office chair uk</a>. Some of the things that you can look for are…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Smart Controls:</strong> </span><span>To easily customise the lighting with your phone or voice command.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Dynamic Lighting:</strong> </span><span>It gets synced with your game and makes it more immersive. <br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>RGB Lighting:</strong> </span><span>Provides customisable colours to match your mood &amp; vibe.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Light Placement:</strong> </span><span>Use lighting in different places, like a wall mount, to properly diffuse it. </span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Decide The Decor</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><span>The gaming room should truly reflect your personality. It is one chance for you to show your creativity beyond your gaming monitors. From choosing the right shade for the walls to selecting the appropriate storage layout, you can do a lot of experimenting. Nothing is off-limits when it comes to creativity,  as you can even dedicate the whole decor of your room to your favourite game or gaming character. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Shade That Speaks To You</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/colour-shades.webp?v=1747048157" alt="Close up of a vibrant color palette fan deck displaying various shades and tones that cab be used in a gaming room." style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span><meta charset="utf-8">From different themes to solid and bold colours, you can do a lot with your gaming room walls. In case you are a streamer, choosing the right colour scheme or wallpaper for your room becomes extremely important as a lot of people are going to watch it. You are not going to paint your room every day, so pick a theme or colour that truly matches your personality and <a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/blogs/inspiration/top-home-office-furniture-ideas-for-comfort-and-productivity" title="home office furniture">home office furniture</a>. Here are a few things to keep in mind while doing the decor…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Personalise</strong>: </span><span>Your wall colour should match your personality so, match the mood.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Paint Finish</strong>: </span><span>Avoid glossy paints as they can reflect light and cause distraction.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Match With Lights:</strong> </span><span>The wall colour should complement your lights.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Shelves To Display Your Collection</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Retro VHS tapes stacked on a shelf with an alarm clock and miniature figures placed in a gamaing room." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/shelves-in-gaming-room.webp?v=1747048192" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span>From old gaming consoles to your aged headphones, they are not meant to be stacked away in your attic or basement &amp; can be the showpieces that truly help you personalise your gaming room. It's all about choosing the right storage for your accessories, which can truly enhance your gaming room’s decor. From <a rel="noopener" title="storage shelves for room" href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/collections/bookcases" target="_blank">floating shelves</a> to transparent cabinets, you have a lot of options. Some things to look for are…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Theme Integration:</strong> </span><span>Choose a storage that complements your room’s theme.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Organisation</strong>: </span><span>In the end, storage helps you organise so prioritise that.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Ease of Use: </strong><span>Go for storage with easy accessibility to avoid inconvenience. </span>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Posters &amp; Paintings</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Cool gaming room with various anime art frame, neon lights, and collectible figures on shelves." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/posters-and-paintings.webp?v=1747045825" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span>From Star Wars porters to anime bobbleheads, decoration is all about giving time and making an effort. You can truly make the gaming room yours by adding a personal touch to the whole space. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span><strong>Wall art, neon signs or posters &amp; paintings, you can choose what suits your liking</strong>. You are going to spend a lot of time in this room so choose articles that you can relate to and personally adore, like your favourite gaming character or movie poster. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>These items not only elevate your room's decor but also your mood and ultimately help you become a good gamer. </span></p>
<h2><strong>Some Extras To Be Extra</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><span>With the increasing competition in the gaming industry, you can’t expect yourself to be on top without doing something extra. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>You can always experiment with different pieces of furniture as well as various interior styles to give yourself the ultimate comfort and convenience to focus on your gameplay. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span><strong>From cosy bean bags to <a rel="noopener" title="Comfortable recliner chairs or barcaloungers" href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/collections/recliner-chair" target="_blank">relaxing recliners</a>, you can even put a bed in your room to relax between your gaming sessions. </strong> It’s your space, so design it in a way that helps you get the most out of it. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Soundproofing? Sounds Interesting!</strong></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;"><img alt="Person wearing gaming headphones from behind, intensely playing a video game in a gaming room." src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0564/3452/4316/files/soundproof-system.webp?v=1747047296" style="margin-bottom: 16px; float: none;"></div>
<p dir="ltr"><span></span><span></span><span>Everything about games is great. From immersive storytelling to the freedom of becoming anyone, as Lisa Su said, </span><span>“</span><span>Gaming brings people together”. But, sometimes while playing the game passionately, we tend to forget that we live in a house with neighbours around. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>To avoid their complaints about loud music or sudden yelps or sighs, soundproof your room. </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>You can professionally do it, or it can be done on a budget by using simple things like curtains, furniture or rugs. </span><span>Things that you can look for when soundproofing are…</span></p>
<ul>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Acoustic Panels:</strong> </span><span>They absorb sound and reduce echo. <br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<span><strong>Floor Soundproofing:</strong> </span><span>Absorbs foot vibrations and any other sound.<br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Door &amp; Window Sealing: </strong><span>Prevents external noise from coming in and vice versa.  <br><br></span>
</li>
<li role="presentation" dir="ltr">
<strong>Furniture</strong><span>: Things like shelves, couches or any other furniture that can absorb sound. </span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><meta charset="utf-8">Gamers are known as creatures of habit. A dedicated space that is designed to fulfil all your gaming needs can increase your focus and give you an edge against your competitors. As you know, styling any space is a continuous process and takes a lot of time and effort. So, don’t be hasty, as there are a lot of things involved that can’t be changed every day. We hope that this article about gaming room ideas gave you some pointers about choosing different items for your room to make your dream gaming setup. </p>
<h2><strong>FAQs:</strong></h2>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>How to build a gaming setup?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>Gaming room setups can be as small as a chair and a pc or as elaborate as the royal family's Christmas traditions. The sky is the limit when it comes to choosing accessories and their features for your gaming setup. In general, the gaming room setup consists of additions like a monitor, keyboard, mouse and headphones with a mic to communicate while gaming. A dedicated chair and desk can be bought to make the setup more comfortable. In case you are on a budget, you can go for our economical </span><a href="https://dreamhomestore.co.uk/collections/gaming-chairs" title="gaming chairs"><span>gaming chairs</span></a><span> &amp; </span><span>desks</span><span> that deliver comfort without breaking the bank. </span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>How to decorate a gaming room?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>The gaming room should be decorated in a way that reflects your personality. You can go for different themes, based on a game you like or a character you relate to. Solid colours can also be mixed and matched to turn your gaming room into a style statement. You can also showcase your accessories on shelves with different posters or paintings on the wall. When it comes to decorating any space, nothing is off-limits as long as you don’t start feeling overwhelmed with it. Focus on fixed things like lighting or wall colour more than the variables like shelves or cabinets, as you can’t change the fixed things easily. </span><b></b></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>How to soundproof a gaming room on a budget with a gaming chair in the UK?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span>Generally, people think that soundproofing is always an expensive thing to do. It is quite right because if you get professional help, it can cost you from £300 to £2,000 or more, depending on your room size. But, focusing on small things like </span><span>setup placement</span><span> or </span><span>furniture choices</span><span> can make a lot of difference. Decorate your room with</span><span> </span><span>thick rugs and curtains</span><span> along with fabric </span><span>upholstered furniture</span><span> that minimises the eco and absorbs a lot of sound. These are not the perfect solution, but can help you focus on the games. </span></p>
<p> </p>
          
